    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix serving network name null termination in NAS security functions\n\n### Summary\nThe `servingNetworkName()` function in the NAS security implementation was not properly null-terminating the constructed network name string, causing incorrect length calculations in downstream functions. This led to data corruption when computing security keys.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/nr_common.c`: Added null terminator after constructing serving network name string\n\n### Reproduction\nWithout this fix, the system may experience:\n- Incorrect KDF input parameters due to wrong network name length\n- Authentication failures during registration procedures  \n- Segfaults when processing NAS security contexts\n- Mismatched security keys between UE and network\n\nThe issue manifests when running registration procedures with both 2-digit and 3-digit MNC configurations, where the `strlen()` call in `transferRES()`, `derive_kausf()`, and `derive_kseaf()` functions returns incorrect lengths, causing buffer overruns when writing subsequent data fields.\n"
}